-- South African Coal Export Prices Decrease Most in Two Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-09-17T09:09:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/south-african-coal-export-prices-decrease-most-in-two-months.html
Coal export prices at  South
Africa ’s  Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for
shipping the fuel, fell the most in two months.  Coal for  immediate delivery  decreased $2.93, or 3.3
percent, to $85.17 a metric ton in the week ended Sept. 14,
according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the
steepest decline since the week ended July 13. The price is
quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
